fields.label: Contractor Instructions
fields.defaultValue:
Roof Inspection + Hover  You will complete a thorough exterior inspection of the property, including the roof. An adjuster will not be onsite with you. You will need to bring and set-up a ladder, climb the roof, and photograph its current condition and any damage.  

1) Introduce yourself to the Onsite Contact, if they are present. If they ask you any questions about their policy or coverage, refer them to their Crawford Adjuster.  

2) Arrive on time in proper attire, including appropriate footwear for climbing roofs. Bring all required equipment, including a pitch gauge, roof gauge, chalk, and a long enough ladder to access the roof.  

3) Click Start Assignment when you are ready to begin. The app will walk you through taking all photos and entering required information. Photos must be taken in the CIS app. You cannot upload photos from your phone.  

4) You will need to complete a test square on each directional slope of the roof (ex. North, South, East, West) and photograph the test square. If you have questions about completing test squares, please contact support_crawfordinspections@us.crawco.com prior to the inspection.  

5) Once you have uploaded all required photos and submitted the report, you will be prompted to complete a Hover report. Follow the prompts to complete this in the Hover app. Hover is required for this assignment and cannot be skipped.
